            <quote source="#bib5138-2">Joh. Eph., EH 5.2, narrates that the tritheists under the leadership of Conon and Eugenius attempted to win various dignitaries for their doctrine. Two stepbrothers, Theodosius and Phocas, were sent to Rome to convince the Roman general Narses. However, this attempt was unsuccessful.</quote>
